From: Enric Balletbo i Serra <enric.balletbo@collabora.com>
Date: Mon, 2 May 2016 09:54:23 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2937/4706] drm/dp: Add define to set 0.5% down-spread in
 MAX_DOWNSPREAD register

commit 56c5da00271e656466d34b853d6c2b5f3ce3ee5a upstream

Support of 0.5% down-spread is required for DisplayPort Specification
Version 1.1 Sink.

Signed-off-by: Enric Balletbo i Serra <enric.balletbo@collabora.com>
[treding@nvidia.com: rename to DP_MAX_DOWNSPREAD_0_5]
Signed-off-by: Thierry Reding <treding@nvidia.com>
---
 include/drm/drm_dp_helper.h |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/include/drm/drm_dp_helper.h b/include/drm/drm_dp_helper.h
index 1252108..9d03f16 100644
--- a/include/drm/drm_dp_helper.h
+++ b/include/drm/drm_dp_helper.h
@@ -73,6 +73,7 @@
 # define DP_ENHANCED_FRAME_CAP		    (1 << 7)
 
 #define DP_MAX_DOWNSPREAD                   0x003
+# define DP_MAX_DOWNSPREAD_0_5		    (1 << 0)
 # define DP_NO_AUX_HANDSHAKE_LINK_TRAINING  (1 << 6)
 
 #define DP_NORP                             0x004
